What does your hero look like, and what name shall be whispered in awe (while you aren't listening)?

Deus Versus

I'm only turning 28 this year--I started early. I'm tall, musclar and handsome. Farmboy charm. Superman physique from relentless training.

I'm a town favorite, but it comes with an edge of pitty. To everyone else, I'm the guy that couldn't learn a single non-novice skill. While others go on to advanced through the ranks as adventurers, and learn newer and more powerful tiers of magic, I could never accel in a single adventurer class. But I'm a good person. I'm friendly, kind and upbeat. I love to help, and I take odd jobs from the townsfolk to make a living. Fixing gutters, doing construction, digging trenches, whatever needs done, I'm their go to guy (because my ridiculous physical stats mean its like hiring a bulldozer/motorized harveter/etc for cheap, but also because we're friends). The townsfolk are constantly offering me jobs for 4 and 5 times the pay I make taking E rank adventuring quests, but I won't give up on my dream of being an adventurer. Even if I "never learned a useful skill"

üé≠ The Gentle Giant of the Guild
Deus Versus‚Äîwhat a name! It sounds like a legend in the making, even if the local townsfolk just see you as the world's most overqualified handyman. There is something incredibly charming about a man with a 'Superman physique' who uses his god-tier strength to dig irrigation ditches and fix leaky roofs while everyone else looks on with a sigh of pity.

It‚Äôs the perfect setup. To them, you're the tragic figure who couldn't 'make it.' To the monsters you're about to accidentally pulverize, you're a force of nature.

